The course provides an overview of group work principles, group dynamics and methods. Different types of groups, indications and limitations of their implementation, and opportunities for group work in different target groups are introduced. The ethics of group work and problematic behavior in the group are discussed.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to provide theoretical basis about the types of group work and implementation in the context of psychological help. The practical aspects of conducting group work are discussed. Passing the course is a prerequisite for group work methods training.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Knows the models of group development and knows the goals and ways of managing psychological processes in a group. Knows the structure of group work, principles of implementation and ways of intervening in a group. Can distinguish different types of groups according to their goals, methods and needs of group participants. Can describe the role, tasks and characteristics of a group leader. Knows the ethical principles of group work. Can use theoretical knowledge in solving practical group work planning tasks.
